    MediaSearchResponse

    public class MultiDataResponse
extends DataResponse
    Implements a SLNP multi-data response. It's extends the single key/value DataResponse to handle multiple data key/value maps.
    Author:
    Patrick Rogalla

    • Constructor Detail

      • MultiDataResponse

        public MultiDataResponse(Connectable con,
                         java.lang.String idxName)
                  throws java.lang.ReflectiveOperationException
        Initialize a new MultiDataResponse with an object that implements the connectable interface. The index name defines which SLNP message key should be used to index the data.
        Parameters:
        con - a reference to a connectable object. This reference will be used to communicate with the server
        idxName - case sensitive name to index data sets by a specific data key name
        Throws:
        java.lang.ReflectiveOperationException - if the response message dosn't support the required initialization functionality
